Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting possible reduced renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), which may indicate renal impairment or possible urinary tract pathology. HbA1c is low, not consistent with diabetes, despite glucosuria. No evidence of infection (negative nitrite, leukocytes). Recommend further renal evaluation and clinical correlation for possible underlying kidney disease and assessment of urine discoloration.
